In addition, for fluorescence sensing of thiram, the probe system is also accompanied by an increase in the UV absorption signal. When the thiram concentration is gradually increased within the range of 1.25–103.82 μM, the UV absorption signal of A450 also displayed gradually rises regularly with good linearity against thiram concentration with R2 = 9986 (Fig. 3
                        (e-f)), and the LOD is calculated to be 0.142 μM. In summary, this probe system has an ultralow LOD and a wider detection range for both colorimetric and fluorescent dual-signal detection, this strategy showed more excellent performance by comparing with others (Table 2
                        ).
